[While it is a good step that Pfizer will share a generic version of their anti-viral drug in 95 countries without the threat of patent infringement once the EUA is granted, that still leaves out a large portion of the world's population. China, Thailand, Argentina and Brazil were not included in the agreement. Furthermore, it is immoral that only 4.6% of people in low-income countries have received at least one COVID vaccine dose. Pfizer should share its technology to allow production of generic versions of their COVID-19 vaccine. No country exists in isolation and without much higher vaccination rates, the virus will continue to be transmitted, providing it opportunity to mutate. - Mod.LK]

