[Data by country, area, or territory for 17 Nov 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20 Daily%20 Tables%20NOV17_1637255780.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 28.9% of cases and 20.1% of deaths in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 95.39 million cases. The USA reported 151 953 cases over the last 24 hours. An additional 6 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours (Brazil, Argentina, Colombia, Canada, Chile, and Dominican Republic), and an additional 4 countries (Mexico, Peru, Bolivia, and Venezuela), reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Many countries including Guatemala and Ecuador, among others did not report any cases over the last 24 hours.

- The European region reported 61.1% of daily case numbers and 65.6% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 81.89 million cases. Some countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium (5 cases), Sweden, and Switzerland (10 cases), among others. A total of 32 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, with 11 reporting more than 10 000, 21 reporting over 1000 cases, and an additional 7 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 2.3% of daily case numbers and 4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 16.60 million cases. Iran (6430) reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours followed by Jordan and Lebanon. Iraq, Egypt, and Libya reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases. Many countries including Yemen, Sudan and Somalia, among others did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The African region reported 0.29% of daily case numbers and 1.1% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 6.19 million cases. All countries reported less than 500 cases with South Africa (273) reporting the highest number over the last 24 hours followed by Ethiopia (265) and Burkina Faso (233). A total of 19 countries/territories, did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 4.2% of daily case numbers and 3.9% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 9.84 million cases. Viet Nam reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 10 259 cases), followed by Malaysia, South Korea, Singapore, Lao PDR, and Australia, all reporting more than 1000 cases.

- The South East Asia region reported 3% of the daily newly reported cases and 5% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 44.32 million cases. India is dominant, reporting over 10 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (6524). Indonesia reported 522 while Nepal reported less than 500 cases. Bangladesh Myanmar, Maldives, and Sri Lanka, among others, did not report cases over the last few days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 17 Nov 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

